From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: inthewaves <inthewaves@pm.me>
Date: Tue, 10 Mar 2026 03:17:31 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] [tmp] use gl_version 3.2 for gl_clear_broken Imagination
 vendor GPU workaround

Currently, 10th gen Pixels have OpenGL ES 3.2 in use (PowerVR D-Series
DXT-48-1536), so this workaround wasn't activated. Activating the
workaround resolves MTE crashes from, e.g.
https://registry.khronos.org/webgl/sdk/tests/conformance/offscreencanvas/offscreencanvas-transfer-image-bitmap.html?webglVersion=2&quiet=0&quick=1

Note that as of 2026030700, the test page in question is failing on
36/241 of the tests on 10th gen and failing 48/241 tests on other Pixel
generations (although this is not the only test page in the WebGL
Conformance Tests that is currently failing). Stock Pixel 9 is also
failing 48/241 tests.
---
 gpu/config/gpu_driver_bug_list.json | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/gpu/config/gpu_driver_bug_list.json b/gpu/config/gpu_driver_bug_list.json
index 9f18a8395c4e1..378dbe6419c70 100644
--- a/gpu/config/gpu_driver_bug_list.json
+++ b/gpu/config/gpu_driver_bug_list.json
@@ -371,7 +371,7 @@
       },
       "gl_version": {
         "op": "<=",
-        "value": "3.0"
+        "value": "3.2"
       },
       "gl_vendor": "Imagination.*",
       "features": [
